|2006\u201307]]<ref name=2007LeagueCupFinal/>\n*[[UEFA Champions League]] runner-up: [[2005\u201306 UEFA Champions League|2005\u201306]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/europe/4773353.stm |title=Barcelona 2\u20131 Arsenal |website=BBC Sport |date=17 May 2006 |accessdate=27 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Barcelona'''\n*[[La Liga]]: [[2012\u201313 La Liga|2012\u201313]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/t/t2012-131.html?t=lista |title=Barcelona 2012\u201313: Statistics |website=BDFutbol |accessdate=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: [[2011\u201312 Copa del Rey|2011\u201312]]{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: [[2011 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2011]], [[2013 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2013]]{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2011 UEFA Super Cup|2011]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/matches/season=2011/round=2000258/match=2006776/index.html |title=Barcelona beat Porto for fourth UEFA Super Cup |publisher=UEFA |date=26 August 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181024170931/https://www.uefa.com/uefasupercup/matches/season=2011/round=2000258/match=2006776/index.html |archivedate=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n*[[FIFA Club World Cup]]: [[2011 FIFA Club World Cup|2011]]{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n'''Chelsea'''\n*[[Premier League]]: [[2014\u201315 Premier League|2014\u201315]], [[2016\u201317 Premier League|2016\u201317]]<ref name=PremProfile>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/2417/Cesc-F\u00e0bregas/overview |title=Cesc F\u00e0bregas: Overview |publisher=Premier League |accessdate=16 April 2018}}</ref>\n*FA Cup: [[2017\u201318 FA Cup|2017\u201318]];<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44091559 |title=Chelsea 1\u20130 Manchester United |first=Phil |last=McNulty |website=BBC Sport |date=19 May 2018 |accessdate=19 May 2018}}</ref> runner-up: [[2016\u201317 FA Cup|2016\u201317]]<ref>{{cite news |url=h