turias Awards]]: 2010{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n*[[Orders, decorations, and medals of Spain#Society & culture|Gold Medal of the Royal Order of Sporting Merit]]: 2011<ref>[http://www.mundodeportivo.com/20111005/futbol/seleccion-espanola/las-campeones-del-mundo-de-futbol-ya-tienen-la-real-orden-del-merito-deportivo_54226408413.html Royal Order of Sporting Merit 2011], mundodeportivo.com, accessed 19 December 2011.</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of footballers with 100 or more caps]]\n\n== Notes ==\n<references group=\"nb\"/>\n:.{{note|a}}Records began at the start of the [[2006\u201307 FA Premier League|2006\u201307 season]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20181005203153/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/teams/first-team/cesc-fabregas?pageTab=biography Profile] at the Chelsea F.C. website\n* {{BDFutbol}}\n* [http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/j10217.html?cat=SEL National team data] at BDFutbol\n* {{Soccerbase}}\n* {{NFT player}}\n* {{FIFA player}}\n* {{UEFA player}}\n\n{{AS Monaco FC squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Spain squads\n| bg = #DB000D\n| fg = #FBEA0E\n| bordercolor = #000030\n| list1 = \n{{Spain squad 2006 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2008}}\n{{Spain squad 2009 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2012}}\n{{Spain squad 2013 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{FIFA U-17 World Cup awards}}\n{{UEFA European Under-17 Football Championship awards}}\n{{Bravo award winners}}\n{{Golden Boy award winners}}\n{{PFA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{Arsenal F.C. Player of the Year}}\n{{2006 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2008 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2007\u201308 Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2009\u201310 Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{UEFA Euro 2008 Team of the Tournament}}\n{{UEFA Euro 2012 Team of the Tournament}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fabregas, Cesc}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Maresme]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Catalan footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:CE Matar\u00f3 players]]\n[[Category:Arsenal F.C. players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona players]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AS Monaco FC players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain international footballers]]\n[[Category:Catalonia international footballers]]\n[[Category:2006 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2008 players]]\n[[Category:2009 FIFA Confederations Cup players]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2012 players]]\n[[Category:2013 FIFA Confederations Cup players]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA European Championship-winning players]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in England]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Monaco]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in England]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Monaco]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "WP:MOSNICKNAME", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cesc_F%C3%A0bregas"}
{"title_page": "Stephen West (designer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist\n| name = \n| birth_place = [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Illinois]], [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]\n| website = [https://www.westknits.com Westknits.com]\n}}'''Stephen West''' is an American [[knitting|knitter]], [[fashion designer]], educator, and author. His shawl designs and innovative use of color have helped him become an internationally recognized and respected designer. \nAfter beginning to publish his own patterns in 2009 on sites like [[Knitty]]<ref name=\"knitty\">{{Cite magazine |last=West |first=Stephen |date=2009 |title=Colonnade shawl - Knitty: Fall 2009 |url=https://knitty.com/ISSUEfall09/PATTcolonnade.php |magazine=[[Knitty]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and [[Ravelry]],<ref name=\"ravelry\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ravelry.com/designers/stephen-west |title=Ravelry: Designs by Stephen West |website=www.ravelry.com |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> West has also published a series of patterm books under his design brand '''Westknits'''. His simple, clean, architectural designs have been knitted by thousands of knitters all around the world. Stephen has taught workshops throughout the United States and internationally in Finland, Denmark, Germany, Italy, France, Israel, Iceland, UK. He also co-owns the yarn boutique Stephen & Penelope in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]], and in 2019 he launched a yarn brand called '''West Wool''' with his business partner Malia Mae Joseph.<ref name=\"westknits\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.westknits.com/ |title=Westknits |website=Westknits |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nBorn in [[Tulsa]], [[Oklahoma]], West moved to [[Chicago]] as a teenager.<ref name=\"abc\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2019-09-17/men-who-unpick-knitting-stereoptype/11516016 |title='I pretended to be buying for my mum': Meet the men unpicking knitting's ultimate stereotype |last=Floris |first=Lise |date=2019-09-17 |website=ABC News |language=en-AU |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> A trained dancer, he studied dance at the [[University of Illinois]] Department of Dance.<ref name=\"ng\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.news-gazette.com/news/local/knit-the-big-time-stephen-west/article_edeb64ee-3e13-5f76-bc8e-4bf40c132149.html |title=Knit the big time: Stephen West |last=Merli |first=Melissa |date=2017-03-26 |website=The News-Gazette |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> While in school he learned to knit and enjoyed it greatly. He later recalled, \"I could always be found knitting between rehearsals, back stage and in between classes.\"<ref name=\"abc\" /> West then moved to Amsterdam to pursue a degree in [[choreography]] from the School for New Dance Development at the [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]. While there, he continued knitting and creating patterns, acquiring more recognition for his designs.<ref name=\"ng\" /> \n\nWest regularly publishes patterns, leads knit-alongs, and shares photos on his Westknits Instagram, which had over 174 thousand followers as of April 2020.<ref name=\"insta\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/westknits/ |title=Stephen West (@westknits) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos |website=www.instagram.com |language=en |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> He is also known for his sense of humor, eccentric clothing,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://laughingsquid.com/how-to-transform-woolly-sweaters-into-sassy-pants-called-swants/ |title=How to Transform Woolly Sweaters Into Sassy Pants Called 'Swants' |last=Page |first=Justin |date=2013-11-08 |website=Laughing Squid |language=en-US |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and creatively choreographed knitting-themed music videos.<ref name=\"at\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.apartmenttherapy.com/should-we-be-wearing-more-shawls-12-questions-for-knitter-designer-stephen-west-242489 |title=Should We Be Wearing More Shawls? 17 Questions for Knitter-Designer Stephen West |last=Zimmerman |first=Edith |date=2017-03-27 |website=[[Apartment Therapy]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> \n\n==Works==\n* ''Westknits at Home'' (2014) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985299057}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 1: Shawls'' (2016) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131753}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 2: Sweaters'' (2017) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131777}}\n* ''Westknits Bestknits 3: Shawl Evolution''\n* ''Hiberknitting'' (2019) \u2013 {{ISBN|9780985131791}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:West, Stephen}}\n[[Category:University of Illinois alumni]]\n[[Category:People in knitting]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American textile artists]]\n[[Category:Writers from Chicago]]\n[[Category:Writers from Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:American choreographers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artist\n| name = \n| birth_place = [[Tulsa, Oklahoma]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Illinois]], [[Academy of Theatre and Dance]]\n| website = [https://www.westknits.com Westknits.com]\n}}'''Stephen West''' is an American [[knitting|knitter]], [[fashion designer]], educator, and author known for his knitting patterns and strong use of color. After beginning to publish his own patterns in 2009 on sites like [[Knitty]]<ref name=\"knitty\">{{Cite magazine |last=West |first=Stephen |date=2009 |title=Colonnade shawl - Knitty: Fall 2009 |url=https://knitty.com/ISSUEfall09/PATTcolonnade.php |magazine=[[Knitty]] |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> and [[Ravelry]],<ref name=\"ravelry\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ravelry.com/designers/stephen-west |title=Ravelry: Designs by Stephen West |website=www.ravelry.com |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> West has also published a number of knitting books under his design brand '''Westknits'''. He owns a yarn store called Stephen & Penelope in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]], and in 2019 he launched a yarn brand called '''West Wool''' with his business partner Malia Mae Joseph.<ref name=\"westknits\">{{Ci