1\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 16 May 2015 &nbsp; || ITU World Triathlon Series || Yokohama\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 2\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 30 May 2015 &nbsp; || ITU World Triathlon Series (Sprint) || London\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 1\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 2 August 2015 &nbsp; || ITU Olympic Qualification Event || Rio de Janeiro\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 10\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 9 April 2016 &nbsp; || ITU World Triathlon Series || Gold Coast\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 36\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 11 June 2016 &nbsp; || ITU World Triathlon Series || Leeds\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 1\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 2 July 2016 &nbsp; || ITU World Triathlon Series || Stockholm\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 1\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:right\" |&nbsp; 18 August 2016 &nbsp; || Olympic Games|| Rio de Janeiro\n|style=\"text-align:right\"| 1\n|}\n\n<small>'''Key:''' '''BG''' = British Gas (the sponsor); '''DNF''' = Did not finish; '''DNS''' = Did not start; '''U23''' = Under 23</small>\n\n== French Club Championship Series ==\nIn 2010, only the femur fracture could slow Brownlee's dominance for some time. At the opening triathlon in Dunkirk (23 May 2010), Alistair was not present, his brother Jonathan won the gold medal. At Beauvais (13 June 2010) Alistair placed 9th. At the ''Triathlon de Paris'' (18 July 2010), however, and at Tourangeaux (29 August 2010), Brownlee won the gold medals again. At the Grand Final in La Baule (Triathlon Audencia, 18 September 2010), Alistair placed 2nd, Jonathan 3rd, and their rival [[Francisco Javier G\u00f3mez Noya|Javier G\u00f3mez Noya]] could win gold.\n\nIn 2011, Brownlee took part in the French Club Championship Series [[Grand Prix de Triathlon|''Lyonnaise des Eaux'']] representing the club ''[[ECS Triathlon]]'', which, thanks to the Brownlee brothers and [[Francisco Javier G\u00f3mez Noya|Javier G\u00f3mez Noya]], had already won the Club Championship in 2010. At Nice (24 April 2011), Dunkirk (22 May 2011), and Paris (9 July 2011) Brownlee was the winner.\n\n==See also==\n* [[2012 Summer Olympics and Paralympics gold post boxes]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"AB profile\">{{cite web\n | url=http://www.alistairbrownlee.com/profile.htm\n | title=Alistair Brownlee \u2013 profile\n | work=alistairbrownlee.com\n | access-date=8 April 2012\n}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Alistair Brownlee}}\n* {{ITU}}\n* {{Team GB}}\n* {{IOC profile|alistair-brownlee}}\n* {{SR/Olympics profile|br/alistair-brownlee-1}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.alistairbrownlee.com/}} {{dead link|date=June 2018}}\n* [https://www.britishtriathlon.org/gb-teams/elite-team/athletes/alistair-brownlee_56 Alistair Brownlee] at BritishTriathlonMedia.org\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080612212805/http://triathlon.org/?call=TVRFeQ==&id=MjU5Nw==&keep=sh Alistair Brownlee] at [[Triathlon.org]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080430024633/http://www.channel4.com/sport/microsites/T/triathlon/brownlee.html Alistair Brownlee] at [[Channel 4]]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/olympic_games/world_olympic_dreams/8823053.stm Alistair Brownlee] at BBC World Olympic Dreams\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Triathlon Men}}\n{{Footer World Champions Triathlon Men}}\n{{Footer European Champions Triathlon Men}}\n{{Footer Aquathlon World Champions men}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brownlee, Alistair}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Leeds]]\n[[Category:English male triathletes]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Girton College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Triathletes at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic triathletes of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:People educated at Bradford Grammar School]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leeds]]\